      <memberdef kind="define" id="group__devicetree-gpio_1ga0a4575c3750db76692fd0f817a169b50" prot="public" static="no">
        <name>DT_NUM_GPIO_HOGS</name>
        <param><defname>node_id</defname></param>
        <initializer>	<ref refid="group__sys-util_1ga358bc3e7669c860a98839a51cd526b20" kindref="member">COND_CODE_1</ref>(<ref refid="group__sys-util_1ga111fe4e9d63758262fc6810a782cb32a" kindref="member">IS_ENABLED</ref>(DT_CAT(node_id, _GPIO_HOGS_EXISTS)), \
		    (DT_CAT(node_id, _GPIO_HOGS_NUM)), (0))</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Get the number of GPIO hogs in a node. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This expands to the number of hogged GPIOs, or zero if there are none.</para>
<para>Example devicetree fragment: <verbatim>gpio1: gpio@... {
  compatible = &quot;vnd,gpio&quot;;
  #gpio-cells = &lt;2&gt;;

  n1: node-1 {
          gpio-hog;
          gpios = &lt;0 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH&gt;, &lt;1 GPIO_ACTIVE_LOW&gt;;
          output-high;
  };

  n2: node-2 {
          gpio-hog;
          gpios = &lt;3 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH&gt;;
          output-low;
  };
};
</verbatim> Bindings fragment for the vnd,gpio compatible: <verbatim>gpio-cells:
  - pin
  - flags
</verbatim> Example usage: <verbatim>DT_NUM_GPIO_HOGS(DT_NODELABEL(n1)) // 2
DT_NUM_GPIO_HOGS(DT_NODELABEL(n2)) // 1
</verbatim> <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>node_id</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>node identifier; may or may not be a GPIO hog node. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>number of hogged GPIOs in the node </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
